le/20121204/ARTICLES/121209833?p=2&tc=pg 2012 Novelty reindeer song still has legs]\n*[http://frontporchexpressions.com/2013/12/19/singers-persistence-turns-reindeer-song-into-bestseller/ 2013 Singer\u2019s persistence turns reindeer song into bestseller ]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20131224115919/http://www.csnbayarea.com/show/391546/episode/657736 2013 Dr. Elmo on Comcast/Yahoo Sports Network]\n*{{YouTube|TfSb6J4jhcU|A Remix of the original song \"Grandma Got Run Over by a Reindeer.\" Produced and performed by Dr. Elmo, Written by Randy Brooks, re-mixed by Frank Martin.}}\n*{{YouTube|Zlywn0D1eIw|2016 Interview with Randy Brooks and his famous song}}\n\n[[Category:Black comedy music]]\n[[Category:Comedy songs]]\n[[Category:Christmas novelty songs]]\n[[Category:American Christmas songs]]\n[[Category:1979 songs]]\n[[Category:Epic Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs about old age]]\n[[Category:Songs about death]]\n[[Category:Songs about animals]]\n", "name_user": "JordanPowers95", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(addedCategory:Novelty songsusingHotCat)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grandma_Got_Run_Over_by_a_Reindeer"}
{"title_page": "Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)", "text_new": "{{short description|2003 single by Eamon}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)\n| cover      = Eamon I dont want you.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Eamon (singer)|Eamon]]\n| album      = [[I Don't Want You Back]]\n| released   = {{start date|2003|11|13}}\n| format     = [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 2003\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=45}}\n| label      = [[Jive Records|Jive]]\n| writer     = [[Eamon (singer)|Eamon Doyle]], [[Kirk Robinson]], Mark Passy\n| producer   = [[Milk Dee]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[I Love Them Ho's (Ho-Wop)]]\n| next_year  = 2004\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|QYwyaCd8MyI|\"Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)\"}} }}\n}}\n\"'''Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)'''\" is the debut single by American singer-songwriter/harmonicist [[Eamon (singer)|Eamon]]. It was co-written by Eamon, [[Kirk Robinson]] and Mark Passy. It was released on November 23, 2003 as the lead single from his debut album, ''[[I Don't Want You Back]]''.\n\nThe song is notable for the frequency of its expletives. It also reached number one in many countries, including [[Australia]], [[Denmark]], [[Italy]], [[New Zealand]] and the [[United Kingdom]]. It appeared in ''Billboard'' magazine as \"F**k It (I Don't Want You Back)\".\n\n==History==\nThe success of the single and the controversial nature of its lyrics prompted production of an [[answer song]], \"[[F.U.R.B. (Fuck You Right Back)]]\", by female singer [[Frankee]], who claimed to be Eamon's ex-girlfriend.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1485501/eamons-alleged-old-flame-burns-him-with-dis-track/|title=Eamon's Alleged Old Flame Burns Him With Dis Track - MTV|last=Wiederhorn|first=Jon|date=March 2, 2004|work=[[MTV News]]|accessdate=March 21, 2018}}</ref> While Eamon initially said that he selected Frankee to record the song at an audition, he later stated that his only involvement was in clearing the use of the music with the following statement:\n\n\"I was not involved with 'F.U.R.B.' I have never met Frankee and she is definitely not my girlfriend or ex-girlfriend. The only way I was associated with it was when I was asked for licensing permission by Frankee's representatives, which makes me a writer on her song by copyright law. But I really didn't expect all this to come out of it, they are having fun with it, it's cool but in the end they are paying me for their 15 minutes of fame and I welcome her to my world of Ho-Wop!\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1485731/eamon-distances-himself-from-frankee-track-welcomes-her-to-ho-wop-world/|title=Eamon Distances Himself From Frankee Track, Welcomes Her To Ho-Wop World|date=March 12, 2004|publisher=MTV News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theslicedpan.com/culture/12-years-on-we-reflect-on-the-feud-which-shook-the-world-of-music-to-its-core/317141|title=12 Years On, We Reflect On The Feud Which Shook The World Of Music To Its Core|last=Casey|first=Gavin|date=November 24, 2015|publisher=The Sliced Pan|accessdate=March 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuring the success of both songs in the United Kingdom, [[BBC Radio 1]] host [[Chris Moyles]] was heavily critical of them, going as far as to record and broadcast his own spoof version; \"We Want You to Leave\", claiming that both singles were the product of what amounted to nothing more than a cynical marketing ploy by Eamon and Frankee's record labels.\n\nThe song was included on the Australian compilation CD ''[[So Fresh: The Hits of Winter 2004]]'', part of a season compilation series surrounding the top surrounding the greatest hits of each season of each year.<ref>{{cite web|title=So Fresh-the Hits Winter 2004 - Various Artists {{!}} Release Info {{!}} AllMusic|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/release/so-fresh-the-hits-winter-2004-mr0000859381|website=AllMusic|accessdate=28 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nBecause of the great success of the song in Italy, an Italian version of the song was released. Its title was \"Solo\" and its lyrics, written by [[J-Ax]], were changed so they did not contain any expression deemed offensive. The author of the \"Solo\" reached number 2 on the Italy charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.italiancharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Eamon&titel=Solo&cat=s|title=italiancharts.com - Eamon - Solo|first=Steffen|last=Hung|website=www.italiancharts.com}}</ref>\n\nThe song reached number 1 in the Netherlands and even lead to a parody song called \"Vakkenvuller\" by Dutch singer Hans Goes (using the alias 'Simon'), which was also a big hit.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w363IFss4is</ref><ref>https://noisey.vice.com/nl/article/rdp7gv/ik-sprak-met-simon-de-vakkenvuller-over-het-10-jarig-jubileum-van-zijn-hit-vakkenvuller</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe video starts with black and white footage of Eamon and his girlfriend enjoying a trip together, then it cuts to color purporting to be present day outside at Bari's Pizza in [[Staten Island, New York]]. Eamon and his girlfriend are sitting across from one another while a different couple at another table kiss each other. Eamon's girlfriend starts to well up with tears in her eyes while Eamon is singing.\n\nA teardrop comes out of her left eye and drops into a puddle below, causing ripples to appear. The video then cuts to varying scenes of couples on park benches, Eamon in a sound recording booth, and Eamon in a room as he rips a picture to shreds and throws a wine bottle at the camera. Eamon stands with his back to the [[Brooklyn Bridge]], singing. The video cuts back to Bari's Pizza showing the girl continuing to cry, as Eamon angrily throws the pizza on the ground and then gets up and walks away on a path and the girl gets up.\n\nThe video ends with footage of them both kissing in black and white then cutting back to the present with Eamon walking along a pathway and his girlfriend follows him.\n\n==Track listing==\n===Single version===\n{{tracklist\n| headline    = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back) - Single<ref>{{cite web|title=F**k It (I Don't Want You Back) - Single by Eamon on iTunes|url=https://itunes.apple.com/mz/album/f**k-it-i-dont-want-you-back/id255156004|website=iTunes|accessdate=28 January 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n| total_length    = 7:07\n| title1        = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)\n| note1         = Explicit\n| length1       = 3:44\n| title2        = I Feel\n| length2       = 3:23\n}}\n===EP version===\n{{tracklist\n| headline    = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back) - EP<ref>{{cite web|title=F**K It (I Don't Want You Back) - EP by Eamon on Apple Music|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/f**k-it-i-dont-want-you-back-ep/id255055028|website=iTunes|accessdate=28 January 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n| total_length    = 20:53\n| title1        = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)\n| note1         = Dirty\n| length1       = 3:43\n| title2        = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)\n| note2         = Georgie's Anthem Mix\n| length2       = 7:04\n| title3        = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)\n| note3         = Giuseppe Mix\n| length3       = 6:41\n| title4        = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)\n| note4         = FCM Remix\n| length4       = 3:25\n}}\n\n===iTunes Album version===\n{{tracklist\n| headline    = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back) - iTunes Album version<ref>{{cite web|title=F**k It (I Don't Want You Back) by Eamon on iTunes|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/f**k-it-i-dont-want-you-back/id255116372|website=iTunes|accessdate=28 January 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n| total_length    = 38:46\n| title1        = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)\n| length1       = 3:44\n| title2        = I Don't Want You Back\n| note2         = Clean Version\n| length2       = 3:45\n| title3        = Fuck It (I Don't Want You Back)\n| note3         = Georgie's Anthem Mix\n| length3       = 7:04\n| title4  